<b><font class="print-title">Guild Unity Day...</font></b><br /><br />
<font class="print-sub">Articles / Luclin Events<br />
<b>Date:</b> Jun 06, 2002 - 02:55 PM</font>
</td></tr>
<tr><td>
<font class="print-normal">I'm unofficially declaring June 14th to be the server's guild unity day. In celebration of this day, here's what I'd like from each guild on the server who cares to participate...
<br /><br />
<b>Submit a screenshot of your guild. Details:</b>
- Please use guild mains rather than creating a bunch of level one gnomes in yellow robes (a la Silent Sentinels... /mourn). Have actual people who play every day in your guild, mains.
- The guild can be doing whatever you like, where ever you like. Killing a mob, or doing something funny, it's all fair game, as long as you get as many of the people from your guild in the shot as possible.
- Submit the screenshot to both on the <a href="http://pub106.ezboard.com/fluclin71335general.showMessage?topicID=7455.topic">Luclin Messageboards</a> (post the shot and be sure to tell us which guild it is and give a short description) and here on EqLuclin.com (use the screenshot submission link) some time between to today (June 6th) and June 14th. Please do not submit an old screenshot for this, try to gather the troops and submit a new one within this 8 day period.
- Please do not have any game interface in the shot. You all should know how to do that by now... try to get the best shot possible. This is going to be a little bit of history, so make it good.

Let's see if we can get more than 20 guilds to partake in this Luclin. This is the first amongst several server and guild unity events coming up... more to come.

~Bic
<br />
<br />
</font>
</td></tr>
